; A. Description
;    A list of commands here configures SPI module and receives data via SPI.
;
; B. Preparation
;    Connecting ports with an external SPI device should be correct.
;
; C. Prerequisite Example (abov_example_config.h)
;    1. SPI
;    2. PCU/GPIO
;
; D. Default Port
;    1. SPI0    : PE4 (Slave Select)
;                 : PE3 (Serial Clock)
;                 : PE1 (Master Out Slave In)
;                 : PE2 (Master In Slave Out)
;
; For more information, read a user's manual of the target device carefully.
;
; SPI0
; 1. Channel                   : 0 (SPI0)
;
; 2. Config                    : [ 0 i s 8 0 m h 101 ]
;    Operation                 : i (Interrupt)
;    Mode                      : s (Slave)
;    Data Length               : 8 (8bit)
;    Polarity/Phase            : 0 (Polarity : Low, Phase : Low)
;    Bit Order                 : m (MSB)
;    Slave Select Pin Polarity : h (High)
;    Baudrate                  : 101 (PCLK / 2 / (Baudrate + 1))
;
; 3. Rx                        : [ 0 8 ]
;    Receive Data Length       : 8
;
; PCU (PEx)
; 1. Port Group                : 4 (PCU Port E)
;
; 2. Port                      : [ 4 4 a 5 ] [ 4 3 a 3 ] [ 4 2 a 3 ] [ 4 1 a 3 ]
;    Pin Number                : 4 / 3 / 2 / 1
;    Pin Mode                  : a (Alternative)
;    Alternative               : 5/3 (SS0/SCK0/MISO0/MOSI0)
; 
; PCU (PEx)
sendln 'cm pcu'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 4 4 a 5 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 4 3 a 3 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 4 2 a 3 -pupd p'
mpause 30
sendln 'port 4 1 a 3 -pupd p'
mpause 30

; SPI0
sendln 'cm spi'
mpause 30
sendln 'uninit 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'init 0'
mpause 30
sendln 'config 0 i s 8 0 m h 101'
mpause 30
sendln 'rx 0 8'
